The Institute of Directors Kenya was set up in 2004, an initiative of the Centre for Corporate Governance (CCG) as a membership organisation of practicing and aspiring directors drawn from both the private and the public sectors of our economy.Among its aims was to professionalise the career of directors in all sectors of the economy as well as advocate their interests. On Wednesday evening at the Villa Rosa Kempinski, the institute held its annual dinner. This year s theme was Rethinking leadership: Being Ordinary, Doing Extraordinary . Present were Ugenya MP David Ochieng, IOD chief executive Meshack Joram, Total Kenya MD Anne Solange, Sovereign Group chief executive Koskey Joseph and GM human resource general manager Fred Wasike.